    "body": "This PR addresses an issue brought up by @ivocavalcante in https://github.com/neovim/neovim-snap/pull/54#issuecomment-4064292674.\r\n\r\nThis fix moves the treesitter parsers installed during the NeoVim `make install`  to the expected directory so NeoVim can detect them. I am not sure why they are installing in an odd location, I'm not very familiar with building NeoVim from source but can look into this if there are concerns. \r\n\r\nThe previous location (`squashfs-root` is the Snap's root):\r\n```\r\n./squashfs-root/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/nvim/parser\r\n├── c.so\r\n├── lua.so\r\n├── markdown.so\r\n├── markdown_inline.so\r\n├── query.so\r\n├── vim.so\r\n└── vimdoc.so\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf there are concerns I could copy instead of move, or could re-implement the previous version of this which uses `nvim-treesitter` to compile/install new parsers as a separate step if that's favorable for some reason.\r\n\r\nI tested the fix by locally building the Snap on an Ubuntu 22.04 install. No more issues with\r\n```bash\r\nnvim --clean -c h\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also extracted the resulting Snap's squashfs to inspect contents (& ensure duplicate or unnecessary parsers, directories, etc. were not present).\r\n\r\nOnce merged this should fix builds in the nightly branch. Per Ivo's suggestion I based this branch off of the nightly to allow for testing with CI/CD artifacts before merging to main. I am not sure what the path to fixing main is given the current versioning scheme (unless I misunderstand the publishing end).",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-16T23:37:02Z",
